Agency Name: University of Texas at San Antonio
Category: Job Order Contractor for Telecommunications & Data Cable Installations
Description: The University of Texas at San Antonio ("University" or “UTSA") is soliciting responses in response to this Request for Proposal  ("RFP") from suppliers ("Respondents") qualified in providing goods and/or services more particularly described in the scope of work contained in Section 5 of the RFP.  The University of Texas at San Antonio is an emerging tier one research institution specializing in health, energy, security, sustainability, and human and social development. With over 32,000 students, it is the largest university in the San Antonio metropolitan region. UTSA advances knowledge through research and discovery, teaching and learning, community engagement and public service. The University embraces multicultural traditions and serves as a center for intellectual and creative resources as well as a catalyst for socioeconomic development and the commercialization of intellectual property - for Texas, the nation and the world.  UTSA is a component institution of The University of Texas System and a state agency and institution of higher education. The university is located in San Antonio, Texas, and is composed of four campuses, including a 725-acre campus located near loop 1604 and Interstate 10 ("Main Campus"), which includes a 125-acre tract known as ("Park West"), the Institute of Texan Cultures at the Hemisfair Park campus ("Hemisfair Park Campus"), and the University's Downtown campus located at 501 w. Cesar e. Chavez Blvd ("Downtown Campus"). The Main Campus, Downtown Campus, Hemisfair Park Campus and Park West are collectively referred to as the "campus".  Maps of university's three campuses can be viewed onliine at http://www.utsa.edu/maps  The University of Texas at San Antonio (“University”) is soliciting proposals in response to this RFP from Contractors qualified in the field of telecommunications and data cabling services, hereafter referred to collectively as (“Proposers”) to furnish miscellaneous telecommunications and data cabling services for installation and removal projects performed on a non-exclusive, indefinite quantity basis as requested by University, andas more particularly described in Section 5 (Scope of Work) of this RFP.
